#Text= I think I just came off looking heavier on TV ... that , or people just had a distorted perception of what I should look like in person .

column1: #Text=But that was my aim in going on the show , that a normal woman can actually have a place in the industry .
#Text=She does n't have to be a size 2 nor does she have to be a size 18 .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Another fan writes : Do you feel like " plus size " models are treated fairly ?
#Text=( I put " plus size " in quotes because I do n't believe you are " plus size " ! )
#Text=WC :
#Text=No , I do n't .
#Text=I do n't think that plus-sized models are given enough respect and I do n't think that folks value the plus-sized industry the way it should be valued .
#Text=But I think it 's because people do n't know how much the plus-sized industry varies .
#Text=Hell , Kim Kardashian could be considered a plus-sized model !
#Text=But people automatically assume that plus-sized means obese and that no one who is obese could possibly be attractive , or sexy , or a model .
#Text=But that 's not the case .
#Text=Whitney 's views on production and editing
#Text=MH :
#Text=Do you believe the producers for shows such as Top Model intentionally pick people who are perhaps unstable , for better television ?
#Text=WC :
#Text=Absolutely .
#Text=I understand it , though .

#Text=When I have my own production/entertainment company and I 'm brainstorming ideas for a show , or a book , or a commercial , etc. , I 'll think of what sort of concepts will accrue me the largest profit .
#Text=The producers of Top Model think along the same lines .
#Text=Mass consumers want to see stuff that 's juicy !
#Text=They do n't want to watch boring characters every Wednesday night .
#Text=They want someone who 's fun and out of the ordinary .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Can you explain what types of things the producers allow you to say or not say following your departure from the show ?
#Text=WC :
#Text=Well , the show is not taped live , so of course you 're sworn to secrecy about what 's happened during taping until the show actually airs .
#Text=MH :
#Text=Who selects your best photo for each panel and do you think there are ulterior motives involved ?
#Text=WC :
#Text=Tyra says she selects the photos , but who knows .
#Text=I do n't know about ulterior motives , but there were numerous times where I knew that I had taken a better photo than the one that appeared on the screen during panel .
#Text=Every season girls say the same thing as well .

#Text=It 's interesting because in the last photo shoot I had before I was eliminated , Mr. Jay told me that I had finally figured out the art of modeling and I have successfully pulled off my shoot .
#Text=Needless to say , I was eliminated and never saw it coming .
#Text=I figured it was smooth sailing since the director of the photo shoot told me I looked like I knew what I was doing .
#Text=It is what it is though .
#Text=What can I say ?
